g.text: Re-key stream by user_id, guarantees only events from the same user will be aggregated together
Group user events in 5 minutes and 1 hour windows, events are removed from the window as they age
Create aggregation payload: unique products viewed, price range, etc.
Break payload in individual messages to sink into into specific Redis keys
Filter - discards events based on user defined criteria
Map - 1 to 1 event manipulation, allows to modify each
Re-key - segment events based on new key, allows to look
at many events with the same key
Aggregation - access all events from the same window to
provide one or more outcomes in form of events
Flat map - 1 to many event manipulation, allows to split
Process function - user defined function that allows 1
to many event manipulation (also external from pipeline)
Rolling window are a fixed sized window that is always
capturing the most recent slice of time. After it
processes or outputs, it shifts forward instantly,
continuing to hold that same length of data but always
dropping the oldest events as new ones come in.
Session windows behave differently from rolling windows.
They do not have a fixed time span.
The life span of a session window is defined by the
first tracked event of that window until
a defined inactivity (30 min for session in Snowplow)
